    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Extension gas fixtures, usually for chandeliers, that use water to seal the joints. Various improvements to the fixtures were invented throughout the mid- to late 19th century, attempting to solve the problem of evaporation of the water, which caused gas leaks.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000083267/Myers, Gaslighting in America (1978)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種瓦斯裝置的延伸，通常用在以水流密封接縫部位的吊燈上。十九世紀中期至晚期曾針對該裝置因水分蒸發引發之瓦斯外漏問題而發明許多改善措施。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
